{"title":"BRASH Syndrome","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica/BRASH Syndrome iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Síndrome\\NBRASH","guid":"YLHLEal9M1ZXtliE91m5Xw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Acrónimo → Bradycardia, Renal failure, AV blockade, Shock, Hyperkalemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Acuñado por Josh Farkas (PulmCrit/EMCrit)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"PENTADA CLÍNICA → no es una enfermedad sino un PATRÓN DE RECONOCIMIENTO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Ciclo vicioso sinérgico → cada componente amplifica los demás","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"SUBDIAGNOSTICADO → frecuentemente confundido con hiperK aislada o intoxicación por BB/BCC","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología →\\NCICLO VICIOSO","guid":"9areuR88wI8WlZgEFd4Otg","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"Evento gatillante → hipovolemia, IRA prerrenal, fármaco nuevo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"Falla renal → disminuye clearance de K+ → HIPERKALEMIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"Hiperkalemia + bloqueador nodo AV →\\NSINERGIA bradicardizante","guid":"eRYOXPkflwYQmKUDQi4abQ","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Cada uno solo = bradicardia leve","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"JUNTOS = bradicardia profunda (FC ‹40)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"7","text":"Bradicardia → disminuye gasto cardíaco → HIPOTENSIÓN/SHOCK","guid":"vi2zqa3d1Ugcw9Dj2dCPyQ","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"7","text":"Shock → hipoperfusión renal → EMPEORA falla renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"7","text":"Falla renal progresiva → más hiperkalemia → MÁS bradicardia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"7","text":"RETROALIMENTACIÓN POSITIVA → espiral descendente sin intervención","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Más frecuente en ADULTOS MAYORES","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Prevalencia subestimada → no codificado como diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Población típica → AM polimedicado con ERC basal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"17","text":"Precipitantes\\Ncomunes","guid":"dvo-3JMeG5kBx8Sq4xtFFg","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"Deshidratación/hipovolemia → CAUSA MÁS FRECUENTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"Gastroenteritis aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"21","text":"Uso de AINEs → disminuye perfusión renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"21","text":"IECA/ARA II → retienen K+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"21","text":"Diuréticos ahorradores de K+ (espironolactona, amilorida)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"21","text":"Inicio o aumento de dosis de BB/BCC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"21","text":"ITU en AM → sepsis → hipoperfusión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"21","text":"Ingesta oral reducida → común en AM frágil","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Presentación\\NClínica","guid":"jdbyUy5_3fZsjt_c7F3Plg","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Bradicardia →\\NFC típica 30-40 lpm","guid":"6h7TVpkAdCLKpMgN0Xt7yQ","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Puede ser sinusal, BAV 1°, 2° o 3°, ritmo de escape","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"RESISTENTE A ATROPINA → hallazgo clave","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"Hipotensión →  PAS ‹90 mmHg","guid":"w9UKozPYW1G3h1epGdorjg","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Shock distributivo + cardiogénico mixto","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"30","text":"Falla renal → \\Ncreatinina elevada sobre basal","guid":"8-FVDSAnPjEcZ1znJiSbag","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"IRA prerrenal → la más común","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"36","text":"IRA sobre ERC → escenario típico en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"30","text":"Hiperkalemia → \\NK+ ›5.5 mEq/L","guid":"hM7saSJndUUbBEjZo9Yd2w","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Habitualmente 6.0-7.5 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"ECG → ondas T picudas, QRS ancho, BAV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"30","text":"Síntomas\\Ninespecíficos","guid":"EDVCD6V6n9qFxmQPvvrafg","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Debilidad generalizada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"Mareos/presíncope","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"Confusión/delirium → FRECUENTE EN AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"42","text":"Náuseas, inapetencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"42","text":"Caída como forma de presentación en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"CLÍNICO → reconocimiento del patrón","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Criterios diagnósticos\\N(todos presentes)","guid":"85O6Fm6LCaUc2og4T44FlQ","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"1. Bradicardia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"2. Falla renal (aguda o crónica agudizada)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"3. Uso de bloqueador del nodo AV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"50","text":"4. Shock/hipoperfusión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"50","text":"5. Hiperkalemia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"48","text":"ECG → OBLIGATORIO","guid":"RYBIdMSNaY85U0I8_sqZXw","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Ondas T picudas (precordiales V2-V3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Prolongación PR → BAV 1°","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Ensanchamiento QRS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"Pérdida onda P → BAV avanzado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"56","text":"Bradicardia con escape","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"48","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"K+ sérico → ›5.5 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"Creatinina/BUN elevados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"Gases arteriales → acidosis metabólica frecuente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"Lactato → puede estar elevado por hipoperfusión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"48","text":"DIAGNÓSTICO DIFERENCIAL\\N→ CLAVE","guid":"jgc2Zyg3pbt2CpfqIvocHg","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Intoxicación por BB/BCC → sin hiperkalemia significativa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Hiperkalemia aislada → sin bloqueador AV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Hipotiroidismo severo → bradicardia + IRA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"Hipotermia → bradicardia + hiperkalemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"Síndrome coronario agudo → BAV por isquemia inferior","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"0","text":"Diferencia con\\NIntoxicación por\\NBB/BCC","guid":"goVGl9ygd6W6yRskYMxLcQ","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Intoxicación → dosis SUPRATERAPÉUTICAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"BRASH → dosis TERAPÉUTICAS habituales + hiperK","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"73","text":"Intoxicación → K+ normal o bajo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"73","text":"BRASH → K+ ELEVADO es componente central","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"73","text":"Intoxicación → manejo con antídotos específicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"73","text":"BRASH → manejo dirigido a ROMPER EL CICLO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"0","text":"Manejo → ROMPER\\NEL CICLO VICIOSO","guid":"POZ3COFS-J0XVwrc35G5Rg","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"PRIORIDAD 1 →\\NReanimación con\\Nvolumen","guid":"9D-h_qWwcG-aKc43lx3a8Q","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Cristaloides IV → SF 0.9% o Ringer","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"Objetivo → restaurar perfusión renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"Precaución en IC descompensada → bolos pequeños con reevaluación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"81","text":"EN AM → 250 mL en bolo, reevaluar (NO 1-2L empíricos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"80","text":"PRIORIDAD 2 →\\NTratar hiperkalemia","guid":"EmbnHtwCMH48vRRxjCuC2Q","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Calcio IV → PRIMERA LÍNEA\\Npara estabilizar membrana","guid":"75OuvNuQo3xvGAoPGt9fFA","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Gluconato de calcio 10% → 10-20 mL IV en 2-5 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"Cloruro de calcio si vía central disponible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"Protege miocardio → NO baja K+","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"86","text":"Insulina + glucosa →\\Nshift de K+ intracelular","guid":"yN33h8BTqWDBeYp74-AehQ","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"Insulina cristalina 10 UI + dextrosa 50% 25g IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"91","text":"Efecto en 15-30 min, dura 4-6 hrs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"91","text":"Monitorizar glicemia → HIPOGLICEMIA frecuente en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"86","text":"Beta-agonistas\\Nnebulizados","guid":"cNy7DhLE3vNTHeDV4ylc_g","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Salbutamol 10-20 mg nebulizado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"Shift de K+ → complementario","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"86","text":"Bicarbonato de sodio → solo si acidosis metabólica severa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"86","text":"Resinas de intercambio → patiromer, SPS (efecto lento)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"86","text":"Diálisis → si refractario o K+ ›7 con cambios ECG persistentes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"80","text":"PRIORIDAD 3 →\\NManejo de bradicardia","guid":"KXTMtuL-p8nYi8YN1GS1JA","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"Atropina → GENERALMENTE INEFECTIVA en BRASH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"Epinefrina en infusión → 2-10 mcg/min → PRIMERA LÍNEA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"101","text":"Dopamina → alternativa 5-20 mcg/kg/min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"101","text":"Isoproterenol → bradicardia refractaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"101","text":"Marcapasos transcutáneo → puente a resolución","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"101","text":"EVITAR marcapasos definitivo prematuro → la bradicardia RESUELVE al tratar el ciclo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"80","text":"PRIORIDAD 4 →\\NSuspender/ajustar\\Nfármacos","guid":"WcRSgrE9fjNGsxbLxVOV8g","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"SUSPENDER BB y BCC no dihidropiridínicos","guid":"gFQQn4u2MnqlZHldGaXwkQ","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"SUSPENDER IECA/ARA II temporalmente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"SUSPENDER diuréticos ahorradores de K+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"108","text":"SUSPENDER AINEs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"108","text":"Reevaluar indicación post-resolución","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"114","parent":"80","text":"Monitorización","guid":"","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"UCI o unidad coronaria → OBLIGATORIO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"Telemetría continua","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"K+ seriado cada 2-4 hrs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"Función renal cada 12-24 hrs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"114","text":"Diuresis horaria → objetivo ›0.5 mL/kg/h","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\NGeriátricas","guid":"dsnJL1DE1t-YtqUvbSMy1w","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"POBLACIÓN DE MAYOR RIESGO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"Factores predisponentes\\Nen AM","guid":"jU_zjycDbk5yBwPe89a4ZQ","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"ERC basal → prevalencia alta ›65 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"Polifarmacia → BB + IECA + diurético = combinación común","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"122","text":"Menor reserva funcional renal (VFGe disminuida fisiológica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"122","text":"Menor masa muscular → creatinina puede subestimar IRA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"122","text":"Deshidratación frecuente → menor sensación de sed","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"122","text":"Menor gasto cardíaco basal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"120","text":"Presentación\\Natípica","guid":"qPr1IktQG7SGB6lOuXsk9g","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Caída como síntoma de presentación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Delirium antes que síncope","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"Debilidad inespecífica → paciente no se levanta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"Sin dolor torácico a pesar de hipoperfusión","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"120","text":"Manejo\\Nadaptado","guid":"AxVi3qTyw25yXjye8Cha6g","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"Volumen con precaución → IC prevalente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"Insulina-glucosa → VIGILAR hipoglicemia (menor reserva hepática)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"134","text":"Epinefrina → iniciar a dosis baja (1-2 mcg/min)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"134","text":"Evaluar PROPORCIONALIDAD → CFS, voluntades anticipadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"134","text":"Post-resolución → deprescripción guiada (STOPP/START)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"134","text":"Evitar reintroducción automática de BB/BCC sin reevaluar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"141","parent":"120","text":"Decisiones de\\Nproporcionalidad","guid":"3jxGAKo3InxC1_1OsOkZjQ","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"CFS ›=7 → evaluar LET antes de UCI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"Discutir con familia → objetivos de cuidado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"Diálisis en AM frágil → sopesar beneficio vs carga","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"BUENO si se reconoce tempranamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"Mayoría resuelve con manejo médico conservador","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"145","text":"No requiere marcapasos definitivo en la mayoría","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"145","text":"Mortalidad reportada baja en series de casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"145","text":"RECURRENCIA posible → identificar y modificar precipitantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"145","text":"En AM → riesgo de deterioro funcional post-UCI","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"ZgJXa89PujaHSD9JFwB5Cw","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"BRASH ≠ intoxicación por BB → NO dar dosis masivas de antídotos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"152","text":"Bradicardia resistente a atropina en AM polimedicado = PENSAR BRASH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"152","text":"La hiperkalemia en BRASH es MODERADA (6-7) → no extrema","guid":"6CgmG_YO_j8x5QPzo3rKgQ","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"152","text":"ROMPER EL CICLO → volumen + tratar hiperK + vasopresores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"152","text":"Epinefrina en infusión › atropina para la bradicardia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"152","text":"K+ normal DESCARTA BRASH → buscar otra causa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"152","text":"NO colocar marcapasos definitivo → la bradicardia resuelve al corregir hiperK","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"152","text":"En AM → la deshidratación por bajo ingesta es el gatillante más frecuente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"152","text":"Post-resolución → DEPRESCRIBIR, no reintroducir automáticamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"152","text":"Cistatina C › creatinina para evaluar función renal en AM con sarcopenia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"1. Farkas JD, Long B, Koyfman A, Menson K. BRASH Syndrome. J Emerg Med. 2020;59(2):216-223.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"2. Schnaubelt S, et al. The BRASH syndrome. Intern Emerg Med. 2021;16(2):509-511.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"3. Khan A, et al. BRASH Syndrome: A Case Report. Cureus. 2022;14(3):e23486.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"163","text":"4. Jasti JR, et al. BRASH Syndrome: A Clinical Case Study. Cureus. 2023;15(2):e34803.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"163","text":"5. Ng CT, Lim KX, Loo KN. BRASH Syndrome: A Rising Entity of Severe Bradycardia. Cureus. 2023;15(2):e35620.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"163","text":"6. Sattar Y, et al. BRASH Syndrome Diagnosis and Literature Review. Cureus. 2020;12(2):e6985.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":169,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"BRASH Syndrome iPad","id":"map_2300","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"BRASH Syndrome iPad"}